# Using Spec Files

Specs are the **contract** — not background reading. Use them actively.

## Why specs exist (pre-code)

| Spec | Why use it now |
|------|----------------|
| `docs/planning/implementation-tickets.md` | **What to build** — scope, lane, gates, acceptance criteria |
| `docs/specs/codedpixels-project-plan.md` | **Why** — Q1–Q64 decisions; search Q## before coding |
| `docs/specs/firestore-schema.md` | Field names, types, retention — copy exactly |
| `docs/specs/firestore-rules-spec.md` | Deny-by-default; Callable-only PII writes |
| `docs/brand/brand-guide.md` | Colours, copy, logo — no invented hex or headlines |
| `docs/planning/expert-review-memo.md` | Amendments that override older plan text |
| `docs/specs/builder-ui-spec.md` | Phase 2 only — ignore for M0–M4 unless prep ticket |

Without specs → ambiguity → parallel agents drift. Specs replace ad-hoc questions.

## How to use them (per ticket)

1. Open ticket in `implementation-tickets.md` → note **Blocked by**, **Lane**, acceptance checklist
2. Grep project-plan for feature keyword or Q## cited in ticket
3. If data involved → read schema + rules sections **before** naming fields
4. If UI/copy → read brand-guide + project-plan §8–10
5. Quote **one Q## or spec §** in handoff: "Aligned with Dr. X on Q40"

## When to update specs

- Behaviour change → update spec **in same wave** (Nathan commits with code)
- New decision → new Q## in project-plan (Coordinator approval)
- Do not implement first and spec later

## What specs are NOT

- Not optional context — they are gates for expert alignment
- Not replaced by memory or prior chat — **re-read in each new agent session**
- Not all needed every ticket — use the table above to pick minimum set
